    en: "The New York State Freelance Isn't Free Act (FIFA), effective August 28, 2024, requires any person or entity that hires a freelance worker for $800 or more in services within any 120-day period to provide a written contract, pay on time, and preserve records for six years. The Act is codified at General Business Law Article 44-A. The NYS Attorney General enforces FIFA; aggrieved freelancers may file a complaint with AG's Labor Bureau, recover double damages plus attorney's fees, and pursue civil action. The Act is modeled on NYC's 2017 Freelance Isn't Free Act but applies statewide. Retaliation against a freelancer for asserting rights under FIFA is prohibited."
